
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

msgid "Enterprise Edition"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm_full_name| is a part of the `Enterprise Edition "
"<https://www.tarantool.io/compare/>`_."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This topic describes how to configure |tcm_full_name|. For the complete list"
" of |tcm| configuration parameters, see the :ref:`TCM configuration "
"reference <tcm_configuration_reference>`."
msgstr ""

msgid "Configuration structure"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm_full_name| configuration is a set of parameters that define various "
"aspects of |tcm| functioning. Parameters are grouped by the particular "
"aspect that they affect. There are the following groups:"
msgstr ""

msgid "HTTP"
msgstr ""

msgid "logging"
msgstr ""

msgid "configuration storage"
msgstr ""

msgid "security"
msgstr ""

msgid "add-ons"
msgstr ""

msgid "limits"
msgstr ""

msgid "|tcm| running mode"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Parameter groups can be nested. For example, in the ``http`` group there are"
" ``tls`` and ``websession-cookie`` groups, which define TLS encryption and "
"cookie settings."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Parameter names are the full paths from the top-level group to the specific "
"parameter. For example:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``http.host`` is the ``host`` parameter that is defined directly in the "
"``http`` group."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``http.tls.enabled`` is the ``enabled`` parameter that is defined in the "
"``tls`` nested group within ``http``."
msgstr ""

msgid "Ways to pass configuration parameters"
msgstr ""

msgid "There are three ways to pass |tcm| configuration parameters:"
msgstr ""

msgid "a YAML file"
msgstr ""

msgid "environment variables"
msgstr ""

msgid "command-line options of the |tcm| executable"
msgstr ""

msgid "YAML file"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm| configuration can be stored in a YAML file. Its structure must reflect"
" the configuration parameters hierarchy."
msgstr ""

msgid "The example below shows a fragment of a |tcm| configuration file:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"# a fragment of a YAML configuration file\n"
"cluster: # top-level group\n"
"    on-air-limit: 4096\n"
"    connection-rate-limit: 512\n"
"    tarantool-timeout: 10s\n"
"    tarantool-ping-timeout: 5s\n"
"http: # top-level group\n"
"    basic-auth: # nested group\n"
"        enabled: false\n"
"    network: tcp\n"
"    host: 127.0.0.1\n"
"    port: 8080\n"
"    request-size: 1572864\n"
"    websocket: # nested group\n"
"        read-buffer-size: 16384\n"
"        write-buffer-size: 16384\n"
"        keepalive-ping-interval: 20s\n"
"        handshake-timeout: 10s\n"
"        init-timeout: 15s"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To start |tcm| with a YAML configuration, pass the location of the "
"configuration file in the ``-c`` command-line option:"
msgstr ""

msgid "tcm -c=config.yml"
msgstr ""

msgid "Environment variables"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm| can take values of its configuration parameters from environment "
"variables. The variable names start with ``TCM_``. Then goes the full path "
"to the parameter, converted to upper case. All delimiters are replaced with "
"underscores (``_``). Examples:"
msgstr ""

msgid "``TCM_HTTP_HOST`` is a variable for the ``http.host`` parameter."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``TCM_HTTP_WEBSESSION_COOKIE_NAME`` is a variable for the ``http.websession-"
"cookie.name`` parameter."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The example below shows how to start |tcm| with configuration parameters "
"passed in environment variables:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"export TCM_HTTP_HOST=0.0.0.0\n"
"export TCM_HTTP_PORT=8888\n"
"tcm"
msgstr ""

msgid "Command-line arguments"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The |tcm| executable has ``--`` command-line options for each configuration "
"parameter. Their names reflect the full path to the parameter, with all "
"delimiters replaced by hyphens (``-``). Examples:"
msgstr ""

msgid "``--http-host`` is an option for ``http.host``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``--http-websession-cookie-name`` is an option for ``http.websession-"
"cookie.name``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The example below shows how to start |tcm| with configuration parameters "
"passed in command-line options:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"./tcm --storage.etcd.embed.enabled --addon.enabled --http.host=0.0.0.0 "
"--http.port=8888"
msgstr ""

msgid "Configuration precedence"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm| configuration options are applied from multiple sources with the "
"following precedence, from highest to lowest:"
msgstr ""

msgid "``tcm`` executable arguments."
msgstr ""

msgid "`TCM_*` environment variables."
msgstr ""

msgid "Configuration from a YAML file."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If the same option is defined in two or more locations, the option with the "
"highest precedence is applied. For options that aren't defined in any "
"location, the default values are used."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You can combine different ways of |tcm| configuration for efficient "
"management of multiple |tcm| installations:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"A single YAML file for all installations can contain the common "
"configuration parts. For example, a single configuration storage that is "
"used for all installations, or TLS settings."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Environment variables that set specific parameters for each server, such as "
"local directories and paths."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Command-line options for parameters that must be unique for different |tcm| "
"instances running on a single server. For example, ``http.port``."
msgstr ""

msgid "Configuration parameter types"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm| configuration parameters have the `Go <https://go.dev/>`__ language "
"types. Note that this is different from the :ref:`Tarantool configuration "
"parameters <configuration_reference>`, which have Lua types."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Most options have the Go's basic types: ``int`` and other numeric types, "
"``bool``, ``string``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"http:\n"
"    basic-auth:\n"
"        enabled: false # bool\n"
"    network: tcp # string\n"
"    host: 127.0.0.1 # string\n"
"    port: 8080 # int\n"
"    request-size: 1572864 # int64"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Parameters that can take multiple values are arrays. In YAML, they are "
"passed as YAML arrays: each item on a new line, starting with a dash."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"storage:\n"
"provider: etcd\n"
"etcd:\n"
"    endpoints: # array\n"
"        - https://192.168.0.1:2379 # item 1\n"
"        - https://192.168.0.2:2379 # item 2"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In environment variables and command line options, such arrays are passed as"
" semicolon-separated strings of items."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Parameters that set timeouts, TTLs, and other duration values, have the Go's"
" `time.Duration <https://pkg.go.dev/time#Duration>`__ type. Their values can"
" be passed in time-formatted strings such as ``4h30m25s``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"cluster:\n"
"    tarantool-timeout: 10s # duration\n"
"    tarantool-ping-timeout: 5s # duration"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Finally, there are parameters whose values are constants defined in Go "
"packages. For example, :ref:`http.websession-cookie.same-site "
"<tcm_configuration_reference_http_websession-cookie_same-site>` values are "
"constants from the Go's `http.SameSite "
"<https://pkg.go.dev/net/http#SameSite>`__ type. To find out the exact values"
" available for such parameters, refer to the `Go packages documentation "
"<https://pkg.go.dev/>`__."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"http:\n"
"    websession-cookie:\n"
"        same-site: SameSiteStrictMode"
msgstr ""

msgid "Creating a configuration template"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You can create a YAML configuration template for |tcm| with all parameters "
"and their default values using the ``generate-config`` option of the ``tcm``"
" executable."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To write a default |tcm| configuration to the ``tcm.example.yml`` file, run:"
msgstr ""

msgid "tcm generate-config > tcm.example.yml."
msgstr ""
